<SECOND>PM-Softball Name Game, Bjt,510</SECOND>
<HEAD>It's the `Gramm Slammers' vs the `Hot D'Amatos' in Congressional
Softball</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By JEFF BARKER</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Each summer, members of <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION> and their staffs get to sum up their identities in two or three words. They do this by naming their softball teams. Some of the titles are revealing. Sen. <PERSON> Strom </PERSON> <PERSON> Thurmond </PERSON>, <LOCATION> R-S.C. </LOCATION>, calls his team `` <PERSON> Strom </PERSON>'s Right Swingers.'' The squad fielded by Sen. <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Heinz </PERSON>, R-Pa., is the `` Buy Americans. In all, there are about 320 teams in three congressional leagues. Many of the team titles are derived from lawmakers' names. There is the `` Boren To Run'' of Sen. <PERSON> David </PERSON> <PERSON> Boren </PERSON>, <LOCATION> D-Okla </LOCATION>.; the `` Hot D'Amatos'' of Sen. <PERSON> Alfonse </PERSON> <PERSON> D'Amato </PERSON>, R-N. Y; the `` Dollar Bills'' of Sen. <PERSON> Bill </PERSON> <PERSON> Bradley </PERSON>, <LOCATION> D-N.J. </LOCATION>; the `` Bumpers Stickers'' of Sen. <PERSON> Dale </PERSON> <PERSON> Bumpers </PERSON>, <LOCATION> D-Ark </LOCATION>; the `` Graham Crackers'' of Sen. <PERSON> Bob </PERSON> <PERSON> Graham </PERSON>, <LOCATION> D-Fla </LOCATION>.; the `` Gramm Slammers'' of Sen. <PERSON> Phil </PERSON> <PERSON> Gramm </PERSON>, <LOCATION> R-Texas </LOCATION>; and `` Arlen's <PERSON> Darlin </PERSON>'s'' of Sen. <PERSON> Arlen </PERSON> <PERSON> Specter </PERSON>, R-Pa. On the <ORGANIZATION> House </ORGANIZATION> side, Rep. <PERSON> Phil </PERSON> <PERSON> Crane </PERSON>, R-Ill., heads the `` Whooping Cranes;'' Rep. <PERSON> Alan </PERSON> <PERSON> Wheat </PERSON>, <LOCATION> D-Mo </LOCATION>., captains the `` Wheat Germs;'' Rep. <PERSON> Claude </PERSON> <PERSON> Pepper </PERSON>, <LOCATION> D-Fla </LOCATION>., is the inspiration for the `` Hot Peppers;'' and Rep. <PERSON> Barney </PERSON> <PERSON> Frank </PERSON>, D-Mass., is The `` Penny Pinchers'' are named after Rep. <PERSON> Timothy </PERSON> <PERSON> Penny </PERSON>, D-Minn.; and `` <PERSON> Dingell </PERSON>'s Ding