<FIRST>r p PM-Democrats-Excerpts     06-13 0539</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Democrats-Excerpts,500</SECOND>
<HEAD>Platform Drafters Stake Out Preliminary Positions</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-Democrats-Platform</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MACKINAC ISLAND, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Here are excerpts from the issue working papers released by the Democratic platform drafting committee. They were written by staff and <PERSON> Dukakis </PERSON> and <PERSON> Jackson </PERSON> campaign officials. Rep. <PERSON> William </PERSON> <PERSON> Gray </PERSON> <PERSON> III </PERSON>, D-Pa., the panel's chairman, said Sunday they represent `` a collection of preliminary working papers ... not a platform plank or draft yet.
</TEXT>
<HEAD>DRUGS</HEAD>
<TEXT>
 It calls for mobilizing `` every arm and agency of government ... under the direction of a ` National Drug Czar' to halt both the international supply and the domestic demand for illegal drugs now ravaging our country.'' It suggests enlisting `` every useful military'' means and strengthening the <ORGANIZATION> Coast </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Guard </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> U.S. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Customs </ORGANIZATION>, as well as bolstering drug education.
</TEXT>
<HEAD>EDUCATION</HEAD>
<TEXT>
 `` The education of our citizens, from <ORGANIZATION> Head </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Start </ORGANIZATION> to institutions of higher learning, deserves our highest priority,'' it says. It promises to expand pre-school for the poor, create a <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Teacher </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corps </ORGANIZATION>, increase aid for bilingual education, and provide `` incentives to equalize funding for school districts.''
</TEXT>
<HEAD>CIVIL RIGHTS</HEAD>
<TEXT>
 `` We will rebuild the civil rights enforcement machinery, combat the recent surge in hate violence and cease the discriminatory English-only movement,'' it says. It calls for adoption of an Equal Rights Amendment and, avoiding the word abortion, says, `` Freedom of reproductive choice should be guaranteed regardless of ability to pay.''
</TEXT>
<HEAD>HOUSING</HEAD>
<TEXT>
 `` A Democratic administration is committed to ending homelessness, expanding the supply of affordable housing, providing assistance to first-time homebuyers and preserving and expanding the inventory of public and subsdized housing.''
</TEXT>
<HEAD>HEALTH CARE</HEAD>
<TEXT>
 `` The <ORGANIZATION> Democratic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Party </ORGANIZATION> is committed to the goal of providing, through federal coodination, universal access to comprehensive health services, including pre-natal care for pregnant women at risk, long-term care and basic insurance for all citizens.'' It promises more support for AIDS research and `` measures to prevent discrimination and stigmatization of those testing positive for the HIV antibody.''
</TEXT>
<HEAD>ECONOMY, JOBS</HEAD>
<TEXT>
 `` Reasserting progressive values, with a strong commitment to fiscal responsibility, it is time for our government to invest in new priorities, to achieve a better balance of fiscal and monetary policy and to put forth policies which ensure that we export more American goods and fewer American jobs.'' It says, `` Advance notice of plant closings and major layoffs is not only right, it is economically sound.''
</TEXT>
<HEAD>ENERGY</HEAD>
<TEXT>
 `` We will increase cooperation with our hemispheric neighbors, fill the <ORGANIZATION> Strategic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Petroleum </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Reserve </ORGANIZATION>, provide targeted incentives for new oil and gas drilling, and aggressively develop clean coal technology'' to help combat acid rain. `` We must halt reliance on all those nuclear power plants which are unsafe or environmentally unsound.''
</TEXT>
<HEAD>ENVIRONMENT</HEAD>
<TEXT>
 `` The federal government will vigorously promote recycling, aggressively enforce toxic waste laws and require polluters to be responsible for future clean-up costs.'' The Democrats `` strongly oppose offshore oil drilling in environmentally sensitive areas.''
</TEXT>
<HEAD>ARICULTURE</HEAD>
<TEXT>
 After `` the disastrous Republican farm policies of the last seven years,'' it says, `` the best support for family farmers is a fair price from the market.'' The Democrats' policy `` will include supply management, credit and foreclosure relief, the return of federally held foreclosed lands to beginning, minority and restarting farmers and the development of new uses and markets for American farm products.'
</TEXT>
