<HEAD>Violent Rainstorm Kills Eleven</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ANKARA, Turkey (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A violent half-hour rainstorm triggered flash floods and damaged dozens of homes in this capital, killing 11 people and leaving two missing, officials said today. Governor <PERSON> Saffet </PERSON> <PERSON> Arikan </PERSON> <PERSON> Beduk </PERSON> told state radio that five people drowned, six died from electrocution and two were missing after the Sunday night storm. He said the tempest damaged about 100 houses, mostly in the city's poorly built slums, and caused widespread power outages.
