<HEAD>Motorists Paying Same As Last Month for Gasolin</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The average price of gasoline was virtually unchanged from three weeks ago in a nationwide survey, an oil industry analyst says. The Lundberg Survey of 12,000 gas stations determined the average price per gallon was 100.23 cents as of June 10, just three hundredths of a penny less than the May 20 average of 100.26 cents, <PERSON> Trilby </PERSON> <PERSON> Lundberg </PERSON> said Sunday. Prices per gallon at self-service pumps were: regular unleaded 91.22 cents, premium unleaded 106.01 cents, regular leaded 88.24 cents. At full-service pumps, prices were: regular unleaded 119.80 cents, premium unleaded 129.89 cents, regular leaded 115.54 cents.
