<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Singer <PERSON> Dionne </PERSON> <PERSON> Warwick </PERSON> brought together her show business friends in a benefit concert that capped a weekend of events organizers expect to raise $ 1 million for AIDS education. The four-hour, $ 100-a-seat concert at the <ORGANIZATION> John </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> F. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Kennedy </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Center </ORGANIZATION> for the Performing Arts Sunday night reunited Ms. <PERSON> Warwick </PERSON>, <PERSON> Elton </PERSON> <PERSON> John </PERSON>, <PERSON> Stevie </PERSON> <PERSON> Wonder </PERSON> and <PERSON> Gladys </PERSON> <PERSON> Knight </PERSON> for a live rendition of their hit song, `` That's What Friends Are For'' _ a plea for help in the fight against the deadly virus. <PERSON> Frank </PERSON> <PERSON> Sinatra </PERSON> was to have joined the stars on stage, but son <PERSON> Frank </PERSON> <PERSON> Sinatra </PERSON> <PERSON> Jr. </PERSON> told the audience the singer had `` taken ill'' and would not perform. A spokesman for <ORGANIZATION> The </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Warwick </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Foundation </ORGANIZATION>, <PERSON> Roy </PERSON> <PERSON> Betts </PERSON>, declined to specify the nature of <PERSON> Sinatra </PERSON>'s illness, but said he would not be hospitalized. <PERSON> Susan </PERSON> <PERSON> Reynolds </PERSON>, <PERSON> Sinatra </PERSON>'s publicist, said from <LOCATION> Los </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Angeles </LOCATION> only that <PERSON> Sinatra </PERSON> was returning to <LOCATION> California </LOCATION>. Ms. <PERSON> Warwick </PERSON>, who organized weekend events that included a special dinner and AIDS education workshops, cried as she made an plea for more funds to educate the public about AIDS. `` We've got a big fight on our hands,'' she told the audience. `` And we know that with the help of people like you, we're going to win that fight.'' <PERSON> Elton </PERSON> <PERSON> John </PERSON> and <PERSON> Stevie </PERSON> <PERSON> Wonder </PERSON> made the longest trip for the benefit, arriving Sunday after performing Saturday at the FreedomFest anti-apartheid concert in <LOCATION> London </LOCATION>. `` That is what friends are for,'' Wonder said of his cross-Atlantic journey to stand with Ms. <PERSON> Warwick </PERSON>. <PERSON> Betts </PERSON> said ticket sales for the concert, a sale of rights to the concert to cable television and other proceeds should bring the weekend's receipts to close to $ 1 million. AIDS, or acquired immune deficiency syndrome, is a contagious disease that attacks the body's immune system, rendering it incapable of resisting other diseases and infections.
