<HEAD>Scientists Observe Fifth Anniversary of Spacecraft's Departure</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MOUNTAIN VIEW, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Scientists are observing the fifth anniversary of Pioneer 10's departure from the solar system today as the spacecraft continues collecting data about the sun and searching for a tenth planet. Signals from the 570-pound Pioneer _ slightly more than 4 billion miles away from <LOCATION> Earth </LOCATION> _ are scheduled to be transmitted over telephone lines from the <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Aeronautics </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Space </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Administration </ORGANIZATION> to the <ORGANIZATION> California </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Museum </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Science </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Industry </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Los </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Angeles </LOCATION>. Officials from the museum and <ORGANIZATION> TRW </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, the <LOCATION> Redondo </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Beach </LOCATION> company that built the spacecraft, were to unveil a refurbished engineering model of the probe to go on public display on Tuesday. Scientists assembled here at a <ORGANIZATION> NASA </ORGANIZATION> facility to outline Pioneer's most recent accomplishments and celebrate the craft's role as one of the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION>' most successful space missions Pioneer is the first spacecraft to fly by Jupiter and return pictures, chart <ORGANIZATION> Jupiter </ORGANIZATION>'s intense radiation belts, measure the mass of <ORGANIZATION> Jupiter </ORGANIZATION>'s four planet-sized moons, locate the giant planet's magnetic field and discover Jupiter is primarily a liquid planet It's expected to transmit information until its power source diminishes toward the end of the 1990s. The spacecraft was launched March 2, 1972 from <LOCATION> Florida </LOCATION> and made its closest approach to <LOCATION> Jupiter </LOCATION> _ 82,000 mi