Against </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Occupation </ORGANIZATION>, the only professional group that includes both Israelis and Palestinians from the occupied territories. Most of the Jewish members are left-wing activists. <PERSON> Zach </PERSON>, for example, recently canceled the International Poetry Festival, which was to be held in <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION> this month, to protest the army crackdown on the Palestinian uprising in the occupied lands. <PERSON> Asad </PERSON> <PERSON> el </PERSON> <PERSON> Asad </PERSON>, head of the <ORGANIZATION> Palestinian </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Writers </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Association </ORGANIZATION> in the occupied territories, said the <ORGANIZATION> Palestine </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Liberation </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Organization </ORGANIZATION> favored the terms of the treaty. `` We feel we are transmitting clearly and honestly the message of our representatives, the <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION>,'' <PERSON> Asad </PERSON> said. <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION> refuses to negotiate with the <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION>, saying it is a terrorist organization. The <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION> covenant calls for the destruction of the Jewish state, and the <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION> has refused to accept unconditionally <ORGANIZATION> U.N. </ORGANIZATION> resolutions guaranteeing <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION>'s right to secure borders. <PERSON> Zach </PERSON> said the group would now seek the signatures of additional intellectuals in <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION> and the occupied territories.
