<HEAD>Officers Scour Cumberland County For Escaped Inmates</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By HARRY AMANA</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>FAYETTEVILLE, N.C. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Five escapees, including a confessed double killer, were still at large Monday as more than 75 officers scoured the area for the men who cut their way from what was thought to be an escape-proof jail. Six detainees, including the confessed double killer in the so-called `` ninja'' slayings, escaped Sunday night from the Cumberland County Jail. They left in their wake two small hacksaw blades, an 8-inch-by-15-inch hole in a cell and a rope made of bedsheets hanging from a fourth-floor window, authorities said. <PERSON> Frederick </PERSON> <PERSON> Glenn </PERSON> <PERSON> Evans </PERSON>, 20, who was being held on murder charges, was recaptured shortly after the escape and was treated for a broken leg or hip he suffered in a fall, said <PERSON> Harold </PERSON> <PERSON> Little </PERSON>, a spokesman for the sheriff's department. The others remained at large as officers with the <ORGANIZATION> FBI </ORGANIZATION>, <ORGANIZATION> State </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bureau </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Investigation </ORGANIZATION>, state <ORGANIZATION> Highway </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Patrol </ORGANIZATION> and nearby military installations fanned out to search the county. <LOCATION> Fayetteville </LOCATION> architect <PERSON> Dan </PERSON> <PERSON> MacMillan </PERSON>, who designed the jail, said he was baffled at how the men sawed through the heavy-gauge horizontal bars. `` An ordinary hacksaw would not cut this material,'' he said Monday. `` I've seen demonstrations of it where they -LRB- try to cut -RRB- it with an electric hacksaw, but the thing just goes back and forth and it does not make any impression in the material. ... I'm really not aware that there was a hacksaw blade available that would saw the material.'' The escape apparently was spotted by a police records clerk who noticed someone drop from the center, <PERSON> Little </PERSON> said. Desk Sgt. <PERSON> Mike </PERSON> <PERSON> Reihe </PERSON> gave chase but 