<TEXT>
 <PERSON> Alvin </PERSON> <PERSON> Wallace </PERSON> is going bananas. Or, rather, bananas are going to <PERSON> Alvin </PERSON> <PERSON> Wallace </PERSON>. A couple of banana trees were stolen from his yard in <LOCATION> Greeneville </LOCATION> in April. <PERSON> Wallace </PERSON> did n't bother to complain to police but he did tell friends. Since May 31, a practical joker has sent him several dozen bananas. One bunch was accompanied by vanilla ice cream; another was black and rotten. <PERSON> Wallace </PERSON> said the bananas have been delivered to his office at G & amp; W Hauling and Rigging through a courier service sworn to secrecy. He thinks he's narrowed down the culprit to a fishing buddy; an empty box containing only the message `` blue gill'' was delivered Monday. He has reciprocated with a couple of shipments of his own _ banana pudding and banana bread. `` Now it's my turn,'' he said.
