 `` Orphans'' -LRB- <ORGANIZATION> Lorimar </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Home </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Video </ORGANIZATION>, VHS-Beta: $ 79.95, Rated R -RRB- The comical mugging that opens the 1987 film `` Orphans'' indicates the dark humor to follow, but does nothing to prepare you for the flip side _ the frightened, frightening relationship between the hotheaded mugger and his younger brother, orphans who keep out the world in a big decaying house in <LOCATION> Newark </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> N.J </LOCATION>. The actors in <PERSON> Alan </PERSON> <PERSON> J. </PERSON> <PERSON> Pakula </PERSON>'s movie _ <PERSON> Albert </PERSON> <PERSON> Finney </PERSON>, <PERSON> Matthew </PERSON> <PERSON> Modine </PERSON> and <PERSON> Kevin </PERSON> <PERSON> Anderson </PERSON> _ turn out stunning performances in a play-like movie based on <PERSON> Lyle </PERSON> <PERSON> Kessler </PERSON>'s award-winning stage drama. The older brother -LRB- <PERSON> Modine </PERSON> -RRB- builds a cocoon, venturing out to make a living mugging and stealing and virtually imprisoning his brother -LRB- <PERSON> Anderson </PERSON> -RRB- by telling him he will have an allergic reaction and die if he goes outdoors. Into their violent, unreal world comes a staggeringly drunk gangster on the run -LRB- <PERSON> Finney </PERSON> -RRB-, himself an orphan and able in a flash to dissect the complicated relationship he finds in the brothers' littered house The story is implausible but it does n't matter much as you watch what inevitably follows the disarming gangster's intrusion into the orphans' lives. <PERSON> Modine </PERSON>'s character, who believes he's abducted the gangster and intends to hold him for ransom, sums it up when he says, `` He's taking over. ... He's supposed to be a kidnap victim.'' _ By <PERSON> Mary </PERSON> <PERSON> MacVean </PERSON>, <ORGANIZATION> Associated </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Press </ORGANIZATION> Writer.
