<TEXT>
 `` Prick Up Your Ears'' -LRB- Virgin Vision, VHS-Beta: $ 79.95, Rated R -RRB- A story of talent and torment, `` Prick Up Your Ears'' tells the real-life story of British playwright <PERSON> Joe </PERSON> <PERSON> Orton </PERSON>'s rise from a working class background, to the heights of success, to a brutal end. <PERSON> Orton </PERSON> -LRB- <PERSON> Gary </PERSON> <PERSON> Oldman </PERSON> -RRB- was a raw talent with a lust for life who studied drama in <LOCATION> London </LOCATION>. There, he met <PERSON> Kenneth </PERSON> <PERSON> Halliwell </PERSON> -LRB- <PERSON> Alfred </PERSON> <PERSON> Molina </PERSON> -RRB-, a more cultured writer who becomes his homosexual lover. The two lead a closet existence before they're jailed in different prisons for defacing library books. <PERSON> Orton </PERSON> uses the separation to grow on his own, becoming one of the brightest talents in <LOCATION> London </LOCATION> after his release. His career skyrockets when he connects with high-powered agent <PERSON> Peggy </PERSON> <PERSON> Ramsay </PERSON> -LRB- <PERSON> Vanessa </PERSON> <PERSON> Redgrave </PERSON> -RRB-. She nurtures his talents, arranging for him to meet <PERSON> Paul </PERSON> <PERSON> McCartney </PERSON> for a screenplay about The Beatles. Success drives the wedge deeper between <PERSON> Orton </PERSON> and his jealous roommate, <PERSON> Halliwell </PERSON>, a psychotic whose mother died of a wasp sting when he was a child and whose father committed suicide. <PERSON> Halliwell </PERSON> is being left behind, covering his disappointment as clumsily as he covers his bald head with an ill-fitting wig. The emotions boil over to dark rage. To make sure he does n't lose his lover, <PERSON> Halliwell </PERSON> hammers him to death in a grisly scene, then takes his own life. The 111-minute video is rated R, mainly for homosexual love scenes and shadowy men's room sex. _ By <PERSON> Robert </PERSON> <PERSON> Dvorchak </PERSON>, <ORGANIZATION> AP </ORGANIZATION> National Writer.
