<DATELINE>VIENNA, Austria (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> OPEC </ORGANIZATION> members have recessed their midyear conference until Tuesday so the 13-nation cartel's oil ministers could informally discuss disagreements over a proposed new quota in production. The conference opened Saturday and was recessed after Sunday's meeting until Tuesday morning Afterwards, two Arab oil ministers left, with one expected to return by Tuesday but the other saying he might not. The Organization of Petroleum Exporting Countries ministers have been considering whether to change an existing agreement among 12 of the members that limits the cartel's oil output to 15.06 million barrels a day. That quota, which was extended in December and expires June 30, was aimed at supporting oil prices at $ 18 a barrel but prices have been well below that.
</TEXT>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Despite the biggest increase in food costs since January, wholesale prices rose a moderate 0.5 percent in May, the government said. The report, issued Friday, supported beliefs that inflation is accelerating but not dangerously. The rise in the <ORGANIZATION> Labor </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION>'s producer price index for finished goods in May was halfway between a 0.4 percent increase in April and a 0.6 percent jump in March.
