0. In the tax-exempt market, prices of municipal bonds rose 3-16 point, according to the Bond Buyer Municipal Bond Index. Yields on three-month <ORGANIZATION> Treasury </ORGANIZATION> bills fell 1 basis point to 6.44 percent, six-month bills rose a basis point to 6.66 percent and one-year bills were unchanged at 6.94 percent. A basis point is one-hundredth of a percentage point. The federal funds rate, the interest on overnight loans between banks, was quoted late in the day at 7 -LCB- percent, up from 75-16 percent late Friday.
