<HEAD>Bank Of New York, Irving to Meet in Takeover Dispute</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Top officials of <ORGANIZATION> Irving </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>. <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> plan to meet Wednesday to see if they can resolve their bitter takeover dispute, the companies disclosed Monday <PERSON> Irving </PERSON> <PERSON> Bank </PERSON>, the target of a hostile $ 1.1 billion takeover bid by <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION>, proposed the meeting after a state <ORGANIZATION> Supreme </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION> justice, <PERSON> Herman </PERSON> <PERSON> Cahn </PERSON>, informally suggested the two sides explore whether there was any way to conclude the dispute on a friendly basis, <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> spokesman <PERSON> Owen </PERSON> <PERSON> Brady </PERSON> said. <PERSON> Cahn </PERSON> is hearing one of several suits that have been filed in the case. The meeting is to include the chairman of each company as well as two board members from each concern who are not employees of the company. <PERSON> Brady </PERSON> cautioned that he did not expect <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> to bring any new proposals to the meeting, and indicated he did not believe <PERSON> Irving </PERSON>'s willingness to meet necessarily signaled the end of its resistance to the hostile bid. Telephone calls to <PERSON> Irving </PERSON> after business hours on Monday were not answered. In trading Monday on the <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZ